OL,7,FThe teenager pleaded guilty to murder
OL,8,Fand terrorism and is currently serving
OL,9,Fa life sentence.
OL,11,FAcross the trial the court heard the
OL,12,Fschool was concerned about a drawing
OL,13,Fof a gun, bullet and wounded man,
OL,14,Faccompanied by desperate phrases, on a
OL,15,Fpiece of his work.
OL,17,FBut despite a brief meeting with
OL,18,Fteachers, Mr and Ms Crumbley declined
OL,19,Fto take Ethan home.
